Johannesburg residents woke up to heavy rains and flooding in certain parts of the city. JOHANNESBURG - There's localised flooding in many parts of Johannesburg on Saturday morning. This after persistent heavy downpours overnight. READ: Motorists cautioned as rains flood Joburg roads JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar is cautioning drivers who will be on the roads, to be vigilant. The SA Weather Service issued an alert, saying that heavy rain could lead to localised flooding in Johannesburg, Midvaal and Ekurhuleni.